// Given a sorted array of n integers and an integer k,
// count pairs (i, j) with i < j and arr[i] + arr[j] < k.
// Constraints: 1 <= n <= 2e5, 0 <= arr[i] <= 1e9, 1 <= k <= 2e9
// Example: arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5], k = 7 => 6
// Valid pairs: (1,2),(1,3),(1,4),(1,5),(2,3),(2,4)

